Photocurrent responses
The CdQ materials are usually photoelectric active and have been interesting until now for their application in photoelectronic materials, but such property has been seldom studied for the cadmium chalcogenido clusters with charge transfer property based on our knowledge. To reveal the photoelectric activity of the charge transfer compounds, a three electrodes photoelectrochemical cell was constructed (a more detailed description is given in the experimental section). Linear sweep voltammograms were recorded both in the dark and light irradiation to profile the I−V relationship (
). The current intensity is related to the applied potential and the wavelength of the light. The electrochemical system displays a zero current platform at about −0.66 V vs. SCE (open circuit potential). The onset potentials of the dark current are at −0.10 V and −1.24 V for anodic and cathodic currents, respectively. Photoinduced anodic current enhancement is clearly observed for the electrochemical system. Photo-enhanced current at applied potential 0.0 V vs. SCE is found about 19.5 μA (no filter applied and the datum deducted from the line in dark). The observable photocurrent responses extend to visible range (>420 nm), while the current intensity (absolute value) decreases quickly when the cut wavelength increases.
